column1: Z_INC02757029A | W9.0, W8.2.2 & W8.2.3 | ACC1, ACC2 & ACC3 | OneDMS PR/IT| Retail Archiving Files are not getting picked up after running the SvjsPARES service and archived into OneDMS ScanView
column42:
Hello All,

Files are not getting picked up after running the Svjs PARES service and archived into OneDMS ScanView

Actual: The files are not getting picked up after running the SvjsPARES service in Service manager.
Expected: The file should be picked after running SVJSPares and archive into OneDMS ScanView.

*Steps to Re-produce:*
1. Login to Omnius via retail channel.
2. Check Serviceability.
3. Add Any package.
4. Proceed to checkout.
5. Fill in required details.
6. Generate contract documents.
7. Submit the order and send it for pares processing.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | Link ID creation not working.
column42:
We are trying to perform Creation of Red+ Group on Existing Mobile Customer and Create Gigakombi with a new CABLE product and check Linking status & observed after customer get activated then search order id in 360 & link id should geverate automatically or on next day click on customer is getting fetched. However it should land on potential linking page.

Order id - 744511

Steps to Reproduce:

1.Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.

2.Search existing mobile customer

3.Added cabel & red + group member 

4.create gigakombi bundel

5.Checkout...

6.Submit order

7.customer get activated

8.search customer with order id in 360

9.Clicks on cutomer

10. should land on potential Link page.

*Actual:*  After customer get activated , search order id in 360 & click on customer is getting fetched.

*Expected:* After customer get activated , search order id in 360 & click on customer  should create potencial link page.

*Expected Result:*
POSFE should not show any error message for valid area code 

Latest Test Details :

Environment: PR/ACC1

Barcode : VDE7601682679/ VDE5601682681

Channel: Retail + Telesales

KIP: 934599847 books KUD
OSF Order ID: 744729
Weborder ID: 4594144 
New customer ID: 934751413

 

{+}Actual result{+}: at X-Sell within Cable a new customer is created

 

+Expected result:+ at X-Sell within Cable a new customer should not be created, but a new contract to the existing customer

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * search for a Cable customer, e. g.: 934782940
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"

--> Weboder ID: 5976910

column965:
15/Sep/23 3:15 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;From Vkdgateway logs it seems that the order was sent to the new customer endpoint instead of the existing customer endpoint by OSF.
From the documentation of Vkdgateway the paths should roughly look like this:
|orderNewCustomer|VkdGatewayService/v2/customers|new customer |
|orderExistingCustomer|VkdGatewayService/v2/customers/\{customerId}/products|existing customer|

-> this is likely not a cable issue but on OSF side.;;;

column969:
10/Nov/23 12:34 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Hari Shankar Malviya added a comment - 
 
 
Hi [~shuyan.luo@vodafone.com]  ,

Based on the code investigation, it appears that this is not a issue, the manual_override_allowed field value is 0 in the catalog_package_subtypes table which is why its not allowing to deselect the hardware.

When the PCAT files are imported, the values of this field are set according to the values available in the PCAT files, so if the PCAT file does not contain this filed value for any stack, the value is considered to be 0.

When the manual_override_allowed field is set to 1 for a fixed stack, then the hardware can be deselected in the configurator according to the value in the manual_override_allowed field.

!image-2023-11-10-12-33-31-352.png!;;;

removeItemAndParseDefault()

availability.hasHighestPriority(1000000, 'GRUEN', 'FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG', 'FIBRE', '(ACCESS_SUPPLIER;DTAG)') == true and cart.containsProductInCategory('FN->FN_Package Configuration->Business Configuration->Hardware->Hardware Capability->Access Hardware->FIBRE') == true

Evaluated = True

CR005943: -ILS
cart.containsProduct('FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG') == true and cart.packageContainsInstalledBaseProduct('20090213_sub') == false and cart.containsProductInCategory('FN->FN_Package Configuration->Business Configuration->Hardware->Hardware Capability->Access Hardware->FIBRE') == true

Evaluated = False;;;

Hi 
 
[~simran.mogram1@vodafone.com] 
 
Bascically, in terms of CR712. we haven’t change in payload (Request/Resposne) structure for any NBA interfaces (getNBA,CaptureResponse, ProcessFeedback)

so Pega interaction with old endpoints or new endpoint must have same payload (Request/Resposne) structure.

Recommend to check in current Pega PROD logs to see is there any ContainerID sent in Pega (getNBA)

For me this looks a new request. and must handle as an improvement.

If  disagree; ask to setup a short call.;;;

05/Sep/23 8:35 PM;gokul.vade@vodafone.com;As discussed with PEGA Team, Container ID value can be added by PEGA side and not required from the Request (OMnius).

29/Sep/23 7:38 PM;shuyan.luo@vodafone.com;*Is this a joke, that you guys assigned this ticket to somebody, who is responsible for reference data configuration :-D*

It is many time said, that with the same version OSE and PCAT, different behavior are given on different test servers.
So the reason could be:
- the (standard-)libs which OSE software included, are not in the same version on different server
- the webserver, or the workframes on which OSE are running do not have the same version or same configuration on different test servers ...

There could be many reasons, which could be investigated by software developers or admins for test servers, BUT NEVER somebody, who are delivering reference datas (product catalogues) :-D

So I would assign the ticket back to developer team, they should write down the instructruction or installation guide for the deployment team, so that the admins for test servers could check, which system configuration maybe wrong due the installation/instruction guide.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1/PR | Back office reindexing process taking too long to complete

2) Select Index Management from System Menu
3) Select all index 
4) Select actions as Reindex Data 
5) Click on submit
6) Observe status of selected index

Expected Result: Back-office reindexing process should complete in predefined time.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC 1 | Completed success (Erfolgreich) status not reflecting in Order Manager sometimes at Package level and sometimes at order level.
column42:
We've observed that Completed success (Erfolgreich) status not reflecting in Order Manager at Package level.

The order is showing successful in OGW logs and at order Completed success (Erfolgreich) status not reflecting in Order Manager sometimes at Package level and sometimes at order level.

Steps to Reproduce:

Login to omnius via Telesales or Retail channel
Perform serviceability
Add Cable or Mobile or DSL Package 
Proceed to checkout
Generate contract documents
Submit the order
After BE processing check in order manager

*Test data:*
Omnius order_id:  732803, 732783, 732631
OGW order_id: 1664024, 1664005, 1663894

*Actual Result:*
(Erfolgreich ) Successful status is reflecting at order level but not reflecting at packet level in order manager after End to end processing.

*Expected Result:*
(Erfolgreich ) Successful status should reflect at order level as well as at package level in order manager after End to end processing.

column972:
16/Aug/23 5:43 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;As per Investigation with UM team--we found the below analysis
While gathering the information from the call I noticed that the requests were being sent to different Minerva instances, we can see this from the logs they appear in.

The successful order 7717071, was made using the minervaRD instance. This is pointing to RNSUAT08, UAT05 and the August libraries
The unsuccessful order 7717076, was made using the minervaUAT instance. This is pointing to RNSUAT09, UAT09 and the September libraries

I have attached the libraries lists for info of this.

The order that was successful, contains from OSF a transaction reference that begins “7717071” and this number is also sent in the <orderID> field of the request.
For the failure, the expected reference is 7717076, but the only order received for that customer (NRW 218944001) has a transaction reference and <orderID> of 5909756


Thanks Alison for the below explanation !!

@Anton Ustimenko, Vodafone: Please can you check from VKD end for the failed order—as it seems Cable is sending wrong  order id to Unity media for the associated Customer

Correct order  id Cable shall send in Request to Minerva for Customer id: 218944001   OID: 7717076
Issue: Cable sending wrong Order id for Customer id: 218944001    5909756( not sure why and from  where its been sent)
;;;

27/Jul/23 3:25 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Latest comment from email discussion 

The audio file was successfully imported (finally after fixing the recordings folder), but not enriched and therefore not send to OSF.

I found the issue in the databases: 

there is a mismatch between REC_DATE_TIME='2023-07-18_12-37-30' and 'rec_date=2023-07-18_12-42-47'

REC_DATE_TIME is extracted from audio filename {*}01c0035a05ef7142{*}_01J33O5I5GAAD9GFSI9T02LAES0000IB_2023-07-18_12-37-30-0391024B-1001534D-00000001.wav

The rec_date is from IRF_USER_DATA_CUST_3.RECORDINGATTRIBUTES (respectively the WDE extension)

For the enrichment process both datetime strings must be the same! 

 

-> further analysis ongoing;;;

column1: OSF Wave 8.1 | ACC 2| UM| Customer address it not matching service adress during Move from VKD to unity and causing different issues
column42:
We have different issues raised for Move from VKD to Unity.

*This defect is to report one specific error related to the usage of adress data in checkout section during Move*

1) in case of Move from VKD to unity, the customer address stays on the old location and is not change automatically to new location
2) The billing address can only be given as customer address or different address. When customer address is the old address, the invoice would be also on the old address or we have to select different billing address


*New defect will be raised for this:*
a) If we change the customer address to new location, we are not able to select any other delivery option then pickup location which is wrong
b) when selecting pickup location, it fails in Sky Ticket



 

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

+To not lose the overview here the list of other issues identified but tracked with different tickets:+

[OS-33582 OSF | ACC2 | Move offnet from VKD to UM | ERROR. -115025: CM-APIPKG0036 - ERROR: Vorwahl für Telefonnummer (1) ist ungültig. - Vodafone Global

TechM proposed to delete the obligated rule which adds by default the product with SKU UMCFUMZUGOP - We are trying to test a workaround from PCAT on ACC2 with Wave 8.1

Perform serviceability
Add Cable or Mobile or DSL Package 
Proceed to checkout
Generate contract documents
Submit the order
After BE processing check in order manager

Omnius order_id: 716993, 717133
OGW order_id: 1639565, 1639785

(Erfolgreich ) Successful status is reflecting at order level but not reflecting at packet level in order manager after End to end processing.

*Expected Result:*
(Erfolgreich ) Successful status should reflect at order level as well as at package level in order manager after End to end processing.

18/Jul/23 1:05 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Hi [~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com] 

Both - VKD and Unity customers are communicating with backend via VKD gateway thats correct.

But of Course OSF should not add prefix KD to a unity customer which always has prefix UN, UB or UH

The problem is not the call to the backend!

The problem is, that OSF is swapping the customer prefix from UN to KD / UB to KD / UH to KD ;;;
column978:
18/Jul/23 5:59 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;OSF is not adding VKD to unity media customer. if it was like that we would have a lot of defects regarding this issue before this one.

The case here is unique, in the request we are getting global id as :LK_....

and usually we will take the prefix from the global id: like UN, UB or UH.

so now we didnt found a match in cable prefix to LK, so we sent to VKD backend only the id without the prefix.

so i fix it now and we will send to VKD the id and the correct prefix.;;;

the request that didnt work sent 2 ids, 1 of the ids was already link.

we retrieve the linkid from the DB and compare it to the TargetGlobalID  from the request. if its not a match the new id will not be link to it. and that was the case for this defect. and this is expected behavior. ;;;

Hi All,


ASB Value if it comes in serviceability I believe Omnius submits but that was part of Cable or DSL
 
We have not hardcoded or designed anything from our side on FTTH
 
ASB is Anschlussbereiches (Connection Area) details. One Area code can have multiple connection areas. This value is received in ServiceAvailabilityResponse (LineItem/Asb)
 
[https://st9-oil-vfde.dynacommercelab.com/Archive/WCFProxy/I08_CheckServiceAbility/2023/7/7/10[…]GWResponse__355eeb25-22c7-4a8c-8918-9d7c13ee897c.xml|https://st9-oil-vfde.dynacommercelab.com/Archive/WCFProxy/I08_CheckServiceAbility/2023/7/7/103739_0h0chvk879sfs7233dhnpkerad/103740_0h0chvk879sfs7233dhnpkerad_OGWResponse__355eeb25-22c7-4a8c-8918-9d7c13ee897c.xml]
 
ASB value was not part of the design.
 
ASB was not a requirement even for GPON which was a FTTH product 2 years ago, this was not part of FTTH design since the beginning.
 
[~metin.celik@vodafone.com] 
Can you please suggest here.
 ;;;

column1: SPN-FIF-000140885 OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1/PR | FTTH(DTAG) ILS orders are goes to 1296(WAIT_SLS) after 1280(SEND_CCB) in COM after OPM processing
column42:
Hello All,

While performing below scenario, we observed that FTTH(DTAG) ILS orders are goes to 1296(WAIT_SLS) after 1280(SEND_CCB) in COM after OPM processing

*TC_07_Perform ILS on existing FTTH (DTAG)Customer using Telesales agent*
*TC_08_Perform ILS on existing DSL Customer and add Fiber / FTTH (DTAG) package using Retail agent and Check Archiving*

*Error:*
{code:java}
1280      FIF          E_FIF_0940010  Result from FIF: FAILURE! 142705::CCM2705 Configurable Service Characteristic 10l13-dAqaAKKfYn with Effective Status: ACTIVE already exists.1280      OP          C_STMC0010001              FAILURE in external action: Result from FIF: FAILURE! 142705::CCM2705 Configurable Service Characteristic 10l13-dAqaAKKfYn with Effective Status: ACTIVE already exists.
 {code}
*Steps to reproduce:*

1) Login with Telesales/Retail
2) Load existing FTTH customer
3) Perform tarrif change /ILS
4) Configure package
5) Add customer details
6) Generate CS/CD and submit order
7) Perform OPM
8) Check status in COM(Effonl DB)

*Actual Result:*
FTTH(DTAG) Telesales/Retail ILS orders are goes to 1296(WAIT_SLS) after 1280(SEND_CCB) in COM after OPM processing

*Expected Result:*
FTTH(DTAG) Telesales/Retail ILS orders should reach at 1290(Final) state.

*Test Data:* 
Environment: PR

Barcode: VDE5601636184

column413: There is slowness issue while Performing address check for ACC1 and ACC2 environment.
column658:
'
I’ve checked the sbusdebug.log for a message with ID:414d51205342554d514d3152202020206493061420b31c9a

That message was initially initially received at the HTTP endpoint of SBUS at 14:18:37,890:
INFO  2023-06-23 14:18:37,890 1116/ 1 [https-jsse-nio-8443-exec-28] request send: JMSMessageID = ID:414d51205342554d514d3152202020206493061420b31c9a
INFO  2023-06-23 14:18:37,891 1116/ 1 [https-jsse-nio-8443-exec-28] OGW1687522717038;23.06.23 14:18:37,891;OGW_ProductService:GetFNProductAvailability;/VFP-002/GetFNProductAvailability;0;;;OGW;OMNIUS;pkgsbuar_SBUSHTTP;
INFO  2023-06-23 14:18:37,894 1116/ 1 [https-jsse-nio-8443-exec-28] sendSyncSoapRequest: waiting 30000 ms for response with correlationID = ID:414d51205342554d514d3152202020206493061420b31c9a
Why exactly the sending of the message took 5s to be seen again in the VFP endpoint, I don’t know. Maybe the network is slow ?

This message reached SBUS at 14:18:42,385, the request was routed to VFP at 14:18:42,401 (16 ms).
Only 4ms later (14:18:42,405) SBUS acknowledges the request.
The VFP information has been calculated at 14:18:52,320, at least that’s when SBUS is sending the response, which is done 4 ms later (14:18:52,329).
About 60 ms later SBUS acknowledges, that the response has been received (14:18:52,388). This response is then routed to the requester.
That is done between 14:18:52,392 and 14:18:52,402 (14 ms).

So all in all SBUS the time between the request reached SBUS and the time the final response was sent, is about 10s and about 99% of the time was
used to calculate the VFP data.

So overall analysis states that this issue is unavoidable as the system will respond on its time depending upon the services request sent from FE towards backend. 

If more services to be retrieved it will take time.

*Sent:* Tuesday, 27 June 2023 12:02
*To:* Horst Froehlich, Vodafone (External) <[Horst.Froehlich@Vodafone.com|mailto:Horst.Froehlich@Vodafone.com]>; Markus Meissner, Vodafone <[markus.meissner@vodafone.com|mailto:markus.meissner@vodafone.com]>; Olaf Greis, Vodafone <[Olaf.Greis2@vodafone.com|mailto:Olaf.Greis2@vodafone.com]>; Bhavesh Renpara <[bhavesh.renpara@Dynacommerce.com|mailto:bhavesh.renpara@Dynacommerce.com]>; Pritam Kathar, Vodafone <[pritam.kathar1@vodafone.com|mailto:pritam.kathar1@vodafone.com]>; Vaibhav Kurekar, Vodafone <[vaibhav.kurekar@vodafone.com|mailto:vaibhav.kurekar@vodafone.com]>; Pramodkumar Chauhan, Vodafone <[pramodkumar.chauhan@vodafone.com|mailto:pramodkumar.chauhan@vodafone.com]>
*Subject:* PCAT SSH timeout solution

 

Hi all,

 

Hereby the solution I applied yesterday on the SIT servers when I got requested to increase the SSH/SCP timeout for PCAT related functions.

 

In the /etc/sshd_config I made the ClientAliveInterval 3600. That would lead to a 3 x 3600 seconds timeout which worked fine for test, just to be on the big side for testing.

We can tune this a bit further for security and safety. For example this below approach could be taken. It does 60 times a check every 60seconds which totals to 1 hour which should be fine.

 

ClientAliveCountMax 60
ClientAliveInterval 60

 

Don’t forget to apply by running systemctl restart sshd

 

Kind Regards,

 

Kevin Dresen;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC2 | CR-525 | Agent role name discrepancy in BackOffice
column42:
In BackOffice we saw some discrepancy in username for "Retail Store Manager PA" and "Retail Store Manager FI".
There are two entries for this role, one entry is in uppercase, and another entry is in CamelCase.
So, during CR-525 testing due to this discrepancy the above users are not getting locked.
Because for each service performed by above agent, omnius is sending one of the two entries to OGW and due to that user is not getting locked after crossing the threshold.

 

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius BackOffice
 # search "Retail Store Manager PA" and "Retail Store Manager FI"
 # observe the issue.


Expected result: There should be no discrepancy in the user role entries.

Actual result: There is discrepancy in user role name entries.

column658:
•	Fastsearch request was getting successful from OGW to OneDMS.
•	Issue observed with Savedocument request via OGW to OneDMS, 
•	Possible cause for the issue - trigger “DOCUMENT_UPDATE_OID” is not working on Document table with ADBM user.
•	Trigger was created on Document table with SVPADM_O user, after that document table is getting updated.
•	Savedocument request was successfully placed from OGW to OneDMS.
column965:
16/Jun/23 1:50 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;issue resolved:-
•	Fastsearch request was getting successful from OGW to OneDMS.
•	Issue observed with Savedocument request via OGW to OneDMS, 
•	Possible cause for the issue - trigger “DOCUMENT_UPDATE_OID” is not working on Document table with ADBM user.
•	Trigger was created on Document table with SVPADM_O user, after that document table is getting updated.
•	Savedocument request was successfully placed from OGW to OneDMS.

04/Jul/23 6:47 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Daniela Sterian 
 
[~devi.jampana@vodafone.com] 

Please find below our output regarding this ticket:

After investigating this issue, we have found that there is a default obligated rule which adds by default the product with SKU *UMCFUMZUGOP* to the array of selected products no matter of which product is selected from the
configurator. Further, when the artefact is evaluating and running the rules, it seems that it fails for exactly that specific product: {*}UMCFUMZUGOP{*}. See attached screenshot below:

!image-2023-07-04-18-46-05-326.png! After we deleted the obligated rule and made the flow again everything was working as expected because the problematic product is not added anymore and the artifact is not failing anymore.  !image-2023-07-04-18-46-35-567.png! The obligated rule is the following:  !image-2023-07-04-18-47-15-995.png!

So the problem would be related to that rule or to the artefact.
Please review our analysis. Since this is not a code related problem, we are not able to fix it, but you can get in touch with the person/team responsible for the PCAT/artefact. ;;;

Alexandra Vaduva added a comment -
 
 
After analyzing the code which builds the contract information and the products / similar products required for reproduction, the following conclusions have been reached :

According to the initial implementation :

Can't find link , products _‘which dont have a charge are difficult to qualify if they are OTC or REC. If visibility is set to “not shown" for Goody (package sub type) then these will be treated as REC charges.’_

On top of this implementation, this new fix

 

https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-14504

 

OSF | ACC1 | Wave 6.3 | TV Winback goodies not shown in Contract Summary in the monthly section

 

has been added which adds all the *cable stack* products in the REC (reouccurent payment)/OTC (one-time payment) section based on the _*'price_billing_frequency'*_ attribute . If the attribute is defined for the product as ONCE, then the product is added as a OTC commercial product. , it looks like that attribute is not defined for the product .;;;

If I remember correctly the issue is related to products that are configured as what we call a "checkout option" (I am not sure there is an official term for this?).
Checkout options are options that are displayed in the checkout process of OSF in one of the dropdowns (like UMP5, UMP6, many technician options, etc).

If my assumption is correct the same problem should also appear for other checkout options that have a one time charge.
Someone with access to the backoffice of OSF can check the configured prices and rates of the affected products (UMP5, UMP6?) and compare them to other one time charge products (SHP for example).

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.0 | Logging out Abruptly from ongoing session shows incorrect message on Omnius Login page
column42:
we have observed that while logging out from the current session shows the wrong error message on Omnius Login page

Steps to Reproduce:
1) Login to Retention FO Agent perform ILS triggering from IPCC link
2) Perform ILS and move to checkout
3) Create summary and save offer
4) Click on beenden button and switch to Retention BO agent
5) Try to logout adding in URL https://osf-telesales-int-acc1.vodafone.de/agent/account/login/
6) which will redirect to Login page with Error message as below

"German: Ihnen ist aktuell kein Shop zugeordnet. Bitte wenden Sie sich an die Sales-Service-Line"
"English: No shop is currently assigned to you. Please contact the Sales Service Line"

Actual Result:
Forcefully logging out from the current session will show the wrong error message on Login page

Expected Result:
If the Agent is forcefully logging out with any condition should not throw the  incorrect error message.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | Logs not generating after performing ValidateAddress service on same address multiple times.
column42:
When we are performing ValidateAddress Service multiple time on the same address only 1 logs is getting generated in archive logs. The service itself is working fine on FE, but no logs are getting generated for it.

 

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login as telesales/Retail agent
 # perform serviceability on same address multiple time
 # go in archive logs
 # observe the issue

 

Expected result: Logs should be generated every time we perform serviceability

Actual result: Only 1 log is getting generated after performing serviceability multiple times on same address

column971: 12/Jun/23 5:13 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;After clarification with Thorsten Lehnert- the ValidateAddress logs for the *same address* should be generated after *each call* of the service.;;;
column972:
15/Jun/23 3:00 PM;kshitij.srivastava1@vodafone.com;Aligned with [~thorsten.lehnert@vodafone.com]  [~andreas.baldermann@vodafone.com] 

When agent perform serviceablity then ValidateAddress logs only being generated if there is E2E flow done. means service must triggers OSE<->OIL<->OGW<->VKD

Basically in past there is feature implemented to cache the ValidateAddress resposne with AddressId in OSE due to performance improvemnt 

so when Agent perfomer serviceablity sytem check the address combination in Cache and avoide the E2E call.

column413: Telesales order process is not completed as documents are not getting archived
column658:
'
The issue was created by by database triggers, that exist in production only for maintenance reasons of the large database, were created under a wrong database user.

There was a full qualified table name in the trigger code which were redundant between two users. That led to the error because the triggers were created in the wrong schema.
As this is reoccurring process, to create/replace the triggers, the mistake has been corrected permanently in the code so that there is a good chance to not face this issue again.

Bas Smeets added a comment -
 
The statement if was fast and now its slow does not help us to pinpoint the issue. This is not a quantified problem but based on a “feeling” of slowness.

The ticket does not provide any times that are expected or actual, nor does it show the network tab to see the response times of ajax calls.. The fact that this flow is not run in performance testing and we cannot see if the same is observed if we test the performance in a proper way.

!2023-07-24_172052.png!
Also we need proper steps to reproduce as the configuration of the package is not clear.

Nevertheless i performed the scenario in my local system and did not notice and significant slowdowns, see screenshot.

Something to point out is also that this flow is heavily dependent on the response time of services.

During the loading of the offer we are calling the following services:
 * RetrieveCustomerInfo mode1

 * RetrieveCustomerInfo mode2

 * RetrieveCustomerInfo mode3

 * ValidateAddress

 * CheckServiceAbility

 * GetHouseHoldMembers

 * GetVFDEConfigurationData (if not in cache)

If one of these services is slow to respond the loading of the offer will be delayed.

The lack of details in the ticket together with the fact that response times have a big influence on the overall performance in this flow should lead to the conclusion to reject this ticket.
 ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | CR-525 | Agent role name discrepancy in BackOffice
column42:
In BackOffice we saw some discrepancy in username for "Retail Store Manager PA" and "Retail Store Manager FI".
There are two entries for this role, one entry is in uppercase, and another entry is in CamelCase.
So, during CR-525 testing due to this discrepancy the above users are not getting locked.
Because for each service performed by above agent, omnius is sending one of the two entries to OGW and due to that user is not getting locked after crossing the threshold.

 

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius BackOffice
 # search "Retail Store Manager PA" and "Retail Store Manager FI"
 # observe the issue.


Expected result: There should be no discrepancy in the user role entries.

Actual result: There is discrepancy in user role name entries.

column152: 07/Jun/23 12:57 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;IBAN validation not working with bank code and sort code.docx;https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/secure/attachment/1073116/IBAN+validation+not+working+with+bank+code+and+sort+code.docx
column413: Its not possible to book KUD products for both VKD and Unity in case IBAN validation is not working as expected -> copy & pase in of IBAN should help
column658:
When we click on creditcard symbol on the right and  enter details like bank account number , it automatically creates IBAN and prefills it.
In this particular scenerio, logic to identify IBAN country check was not working because in this case IBAN is prefilling through creditcard symbol automatically.
So enhanced the logic to identify if the prefilled IBAN is germen IBAN or no so that residencecheck behaviour can be accordingly handled.

Alexandra Vaduva added a comment -
 
 
Hi Harsha/Ari,

This was clear from the beginning, yes, but as I mentioned, the implementation was intended to be like this :

*In case of telesales, if sepa is true, then this check will be shown and the flow is blocked → agent is not able to continue*

Which means that it does *NOT* matter _what IBAN is used_ , this will be shown if the sepa is true and *If the KUD product is part of cable_app_de category .* 

I agree that the way this is working is not consistent : in one case the agent is able to continue but in another the agent is not able to continue.

The final question is - when should the agent be able to continue the checkout process and when should the agent be blocked? According to the initial documentation the agent should not be able to continue and according to these comments the agent should be able to continue .

What is the purpose of this error message and what was wrongly implemented exactly? We can implement a fix according to these comments but we need to know if the issue is that the whole implementation was not done correctly or not, in order to fix the actual issue and not just a particular case .;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | Getting RetrieveDateTimeIndicator error message in checkout for All stacks ILS orders.
column42:
We are performing ILS(change Tariff) on existing customers and observed DateTimeIndicator error message in checkout.

*Steps to* *reproduce:*
 # Login to Telesales/Retail channel
 # Load existing {*}Mobile{*}/Cable/DSL Customer and retrieve.
 # Click on Packet Andern.
 # Add tariff and click on Weiter
 # Add Nationality and click on weiter.

{*}Actual Result{*}:

Getting RetrieveDateTimeIndicator error message in checkout for All stacks ILS Orders.

23/May/23 12:50 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com; 

[~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] [~gokul.vade@vodafone.com] [~ajay.bhavar@vodafone.com] [~ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com] 

 
Marcin Jurczak added a comment -
 
 
The new OIL package for Wave 8.0 release is available: [https://nexus.dynacommercelab.com/repository/oil-packages/vfde/development/deployment/23.05.23.08001.zip]

The scope and content of it is exactly the same as was expected in 23.05.04.08001, but this time it is built correctly.

*RCA:* The package build is fully automated via Jenkins+Nexus. There are 3 repositories, on which a Jenkins pipeline runs and produces an artifact (partial package), which is then sent to Nexus storage. After building all partials, a final pipeline is run to collect all of them and create the full package. The problem is, that the query responsible for downloading a partial is limited to the first 50 items only, and for the most important repository, this number of files was reached on April 17th. A cleanup on Nexus was needed to let the pipeline download the latest available partial and include it in the package.

The permanent fix is to be done: we will need to either change the query to bypass the limit of 50 files, or introduce some regular (monthly) cleanup procedure to avoid the same issue in the future.;;;

column1: NEW CR: CR755 | OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | End price of Hardware is not correctly pass to VORAS because of incorrect HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice in Submit order request for Mobile SOHO Business orders.
column42:
We have performed Mobile SOHO Business New Activation order in Retail channel, In this scenario, VORAS Team observed that Incorrect end price has been delivered to VORAS from Omnius because of incorrect HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice in Submit order request.

 

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Create Mobile SOHO Business RV Package.
 # Proceed to checkout and submit order.
 # Verify SubmitOrderRequest for HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice.

Test details:

Omnius Order id: 700815
Omnius Order id: 782001
Actual: End price of Hardware is not correct because of incorrect HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice in Submit order request.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | OS-17997 | at the validation of the HomeID sometimes the vowels are accepted
column42:
Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1

Channel: Telesales + Retail

Test address: Am Seestern 10, 40547 Düsseldorf

HomeID examples (without replacing the vowels): 0I0IIIP, 0A0AADG, 123123O

 

+*Please note:*+ there are also examples where the vowels are not accepted:
 # AESHSRN (VWSHSRN)
 # A1A1A18 (V1V1V18)

      3. AHSHORS (VHSHYRS)

BUT for the 3rd examle it will, if you replace only the O – > AHSHYRS then it is not accepted, but if you replace only the A it is accepted – > VHSHORS 

 

{+}Actual result{+}: at the validation of the HomeID sometimes the vowels are accepted

 

{+}Expected result{+}: at the validation of the HomeID the vowels should be never accepted, they should be replaced with consonants

 

+Steps to reproduce:+

 
 * load the DTAG address "Am Seestern 10, 40547 Düsseldorf" on ACC1
 * click on "Paktet hinzufügen >> DSL & Glasfaser Produkte"
 * select any DTAG tariff, e. g.: "[R623.5000000526-24] GigaZuhause 1000 Glasfaser"
 * click on "Hardware"
 * select any hardware, e. g.: "[20090211_sub] FRITZ!Box 5590 Glasfaser (Mietgerät)"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"
 * enter the HomeID "0I0IIIP"

– > HomeID is accepted

!image-2023-05-19-09-35-32-446.png!

!image-2023-05-19-09-35-53-978.png!

In this case the HomeID should be "0X0XXXP" (this is also accepted)

 

!image-2023-05-19-09-36-54-117.png!

+Validation of the HomeID:+

0 I 0 I I I

0 x 1 = 0

18 x 3 = 54

0 x 1 = 0

18 x 3 = 54

18 x 1 = 18

18 x 3 = 54

– > sum: 180

180-31-31-31-31-31 = 25

25 = P

Without replacing the vowels: {color:#ff0000}*0I0IIIP*{color}

Replacing the vowels: *{color:#00875a}0X0XXXP{color}*

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 / PR | All FTTH Retail Orders are getting stuck in POS-FE due to OMNIUS is sending adslInternetConfiguration for Fiber/FTTH orders
column42:
All FTTH orders are getting stuck in the DSL BE .

Here we observed that POSFE is not validating FTTH order details and its considering/showing Fiber order as normal DSL Bitstream order . This is due to for fiber/FTTH order *adslInternetConfiguration * are present in Submit order request .

For Fiber orders fiberinternetconfiguration should be only present .

Steps to Reproduce :
1. Login to omnius with retail channel .
2. Add DTAG/FTTH fiber package.
3.Procced to checkout and submit order.

Actual Result : adslInternetConfiguration  are present for Fiber order.

Expected Result : fiberinternetconfiguration should be only present.

Also we have observed discrepency in product code as well .
 productCode I1203 :  Bitstream and productCode I1204 : NGN . 
And here I1204 for NGN technology its showing fibreInternetConfiguration .

Order ID : 699903
column413: FTTH Retail orders cannot be processed E2E.

column965:
19/May/23 12:26 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Divya Kumbla added a comment -
 
 
[~amruta.chougule@vodafone.com] ,The values are sent based on the multimapper defined in PCAT,as we have IG014 in the cart

the multimapper id for this product is 265

!image-2023-05-19-12-18-25-238.png!

And the addon’s defined for this product has *I1203 and service expression is getting satisfied to true because FTTH_Telekom (FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG) is present in the cart here, hence this adslInternetConfiguration is being sent*
|order.containsProductInCategoryId('FN143') == true or order.containsProductInCategoryId{*}('FN0454'){*} == true|

 

!image-2023-05-19-12-20-42-480.png!

!image-2023-05-19-12-21-03-631.png!
 Similarly from the attached xml we also see I1208 with adsl and in multimapper addon’s condition satisfies to true

hence it is sent .

!image-2023-05-19-12-21-44-308.png!

!image-2023-05-19-12-22-02-571.png!

Finally for I1204

!image-2023-05-19-12-22-38-833.png!

the service expression defined as “order.containsProductInCategoryId('FN219') == true”

and again the cart had DTAG making this expression evaluated to true .so the add on value is being sent.

!image-2023-05-19-12-25-54-274.png!;;;

 # In addition to the existing details below the towers new information will be displayed in an additional detailled information accordion "Glasfaser Detailinformationen".

*"Glasfaser Regio-Klasse:" [value from from availability service of AREA_CLASSIFICATION]*

"Projekt-Referenz (Ausbaugebiet): " [value from availabilty service of PROJECT_REFERENCE] 
(e.g."CELLE_2018_04")
"Kooperationstyp: " [value from availability service of COOPERATION_TYPE]
(e.g. Gemeinde)

https://osf-telesales-int-acc1.vodafone.de:8443/api/customer/v3/search?originator=qaosfapi&correlationId=3b38008e-5bdb-41f2-a867-359ec4e37ea3&givenName=Eugen&familyName=Grening&birthDate=1976-04-09&postalCode=84323

202 - Request accepted, but not contend in the response

.vodafone.de:8443/api/installed-base/v3/installedbase?originator=qaosfapi&correlationId=4777caa2-7853-48eb-945e-da91a81f068c&osfCustomerId=KD_93003185]

column1: ON HOLD OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | OTF-774 | Cable VKD and Unity Orders with German IBAN are failling with Sky Ticket when ConvertAndValidateIBAN is down
column42:
Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1

Channel: Telesales + Retail

 

{+}Actual result{+}: Cable VKD and Unity Orders with German IBAN are failling with Sky Ticket

 

{+}Expected result{+}: Cable VKD and Unity Orders with German IBAN should not faill with Sky Ticket

*Please* note:

1. Cable orders with foreign IBAN, like AT391100009583600300 (BIC: BKAUATWW) are not failing with Sky Ticket

+Example:+ ODF Order ID: 698025

2. DSL orders are not failing with German IBAN

+Example:+ OSF Order ID: 698021

3. MOB orders are not failing with German IBAN

+Example:+ OSF Order ID: *698031*

 

+Steps to reproduce:+

 
 * deactivate the service "ConvertAndValidateIBAN" in OIL
 * load any Cable address on ACC1, e. g.:  "Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select any KIP product
 * continue with the order until the Payment Details
 * enter an IBAN with a valid format, e. g.: "DE89790500000080222292"
 * enter a BIC with a valid format, e. g.: "BYLADEM1DAH"
 * complete the order

– > OSF Order ID: *698019*

– > Sky Ticket was created 

Error description:

[HTTPAdaptor] Can not connect to HTTP Server[wss-vf-test2b.kabeldeutschland.de:-1], Status[422], Message[{\"httpCode\":422,\"messageIdentifier\":\"VALIDATION_FAILURE\",\"message\":\"phttp:z3-test2b-web-ibp-int-lb.kabeldeutschland.deapieccv2customerscreate:br\\nOne or more input fields do not meet the constraintsbr\\nDetails:br\\n * VALIDATION_FAILURE: Json validation failure: The property liabilityTransfer is required. (orderCart.debitInfo.liabilityTransfer)br\\n * VALIDATION_FAILURE: Json validation failure: The property billingType is not defined and the definition does not allow additional properties. (orderCart.debitInfo)br\\n * VALIDATION_FAILURE: Json validation failure: The property iban is not defined and the definition does not allow additional properties. (orderCart.debitInfo)br\\n * VALIDATION_FAILURE: Json validation failure: The property paymentMethod is not defined and the definition does not allow additional properties. (orderCart.debitInfo)br\\n * VALIDATION_FAILURE: Js

*More examples with failings Cable orders with German IBAN:*
 # {*}{*}KIP Unity private, OSF Order ID: 698033
 # KIP VKD SOHO, OSF Order ID: 698027
 # TV VKD private, OSF Order ID: 698029

column965:
15/May/23 7:41 PM;oliver.lampert1@vodafone.com;OTF-774 says:
 # If IBAN =German means starts with prefix “DE” then system must by default enable BIC input field as mandatory input and system must allow to continue the sales flow when agent captures the BIC.
 # If IBAN is non German means not starts with prefix “DE” then system by default enable BIC input field and system must allow to continue the sales flow when agent captures the BIC(BAU).

For German IBANs the BIC validation (with OTF-724) should work like for non German IBANs (AS IS). Here Omnius validates BIC without calling IBAN service. 

So actual behavoir is not correct for BIC validation with German IBANs like described by Natasa.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | Sliding charges not visible correctly under Total Amount section in shopping cart for Mobile Tariff.
column42:
We are performing Verify Contract Document for New activation of mobile postpaid with duplicate package and Check Sliding prices in Retail channel.In this We observed that Sliding charges not correctly visible in shopping cart.

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to Retail channel.
 # Add Mobile Postpaid package
 # Add Hardware and Tariff
 # Add sliding charges option.
 # check shopping cart.

*Actual Result :* Sliding charges not correctly visible in shopping cart for Mobile Tariff. 

*Expected Result:* Sliding charges should correctly visible Monthly/Yearly according to charges.

Note: This issue has been discussed with PCAT Team (Thomas) and Also Sliding charges visible with option in extended shopping cart but not available in total amount section.
column413:
Sliding charges not corretly visible under Total Amount in shopping cart for Mobile Tariff.
Impact: Mobile Private and Private SOHO Consumer.
column658: Sliding_Calculator (Preistreppe) is only used for discounts (Gutschriften & Aktionen). In current PCAT no discount options are selectable in configurator which have a sliding_calculator < 24 month. Therefore it is currently not possible to test sliding charges
column965:
15/May/23 3:43 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;[~pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com] 
Divya Kumbla added a comment - 
  when you see the options added in the cart ,the sliding calculator is 0 for these products hence forth you will not be seeing sliding charge as it considers it to be payable for entire contract(24 months).That's why it shows 1month to …
ideally if these components are for 12 months then sliding calculator should be 12.

the issue is with PCAT files.

!image-2023-05-15-15-42-44-671.png!!image-2023-05-15-15-43-19-690.png!

!image-2023-05-15-15-43-29-946.png!;;;
column966: 17/May/23 8:36 PM;thomas.jerke@vodafone.com;The extended shopping cart is correct. We don't show sliding prices for charges (like 12 month MinutenmPaket), as they don't expire automatically. If the customer doesn't cancel the Option he will be charged for longer then 12 month.;;;
column968: 22/May/23 3:18 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~thomas.wermke@vodafone.com]  I think Thomas Jerke is on vacation so can you support us here and check the last comment?;;;
column969: 26/May/23 11:57 AM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;so from my understanding, if there is the same price over the whole contract duration and also the contract does not automatically end after some time (its automatic prolongation), there is no sliding price. Maybe someone from PCAT Mobile team can confirm. ;;;
column970:
31/May/23 1:29 PM;pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com;!image-2023-05-31-13-28-32-223.png|width=260,height=146!
facing same issue;;;

In current PCAT no discount options are selectable in configurator which have a sliding_calculator < 24 month. Therefore it is currently not possible to test sliding charges;;;
column973: 01/Jun/23 4:38 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;As confirmed by Thomas, sliding_calculator < 24 month discounts not available in ACC PCAT for Consumer products, hence ticket can be closed.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | OS-17997 | When entering a valid Home ID the "Wunschtermin" (ASAP) is not considering public holidays
column42:
Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1

PCAT: OSF-20230611_wave7_957_FN_2023_05_02

Channel: Telesales + Retail

Test address: Kreuzstr. 10, 46483 Wesel ({*}FIBER DTAG{*} address)

 

{+}Actual result{+}: When entering a valid Home ID the "Wunschtermin" (ASAP) is today + 5  days (On 18th of May there is a public holiday in Germany)

 

{+}Expected result{+}: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | OS-17997 | When entering a valid Home ID the "Wunschtermin" should be today + 5 *WORKING* days like when selecting "Tag auswählen"

 

+Steps to reproduce:+

 
 * load the address "Am Seestern 10, 40547 Düsseldorf" on ACC1
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> DSL und Glasfaser Prdukte"
 * select any DTAG product, e. g.: "[R623.5000000526-24] GigaZuhause 1000 Glasfaser"
 * select any hardware, e. g.: "[20090211_sub] FRITZ!Box 5590 Glasfaser (Mietgerät)"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"
 * enter an invalid HomeID, e. g.: "222WDXQ"

– > "Schnellstmöglich" (ASAP) is preselected in the field "Wunschtermin" – > *OK*

– > the preselected date is today + 5 OR today + 4 *WORKING* days – > *NOT* *OK* (on 18th of May there is a public holiday in Germany)

!image-2023-05-11-13-31-55-899.png!
 * select "Tag auswählen" in the field "Wunschtermin"
 * open the calendar in the date field 

– > 19th of May can be selected as the earliest date instead of 18th of May – > *OK*

!image-2023-05-11-13-32-29-511.png!

Wehen entering an invalid IBAN and a valid BIC, data can be saved:

!image-2023-05-13-08-37-08-727.png!

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave8.0| Unable to search saved shopping cart for Mobile SOHO Business.
column42:
While performing Customer search scenario by using Customer details in Retail *(Customer_Type: SOHO Bussiness)* channel with Mobile Postpaid, In this scenario, We have observed, save and send shopping card  customer is not search.

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Select Customer Type SOHO Bussiness.
 # Select Mobile Subscription.
 # Add Hardware and Tarif.
 # Click on Dublicate Package and click on "Weiter" button.
 # Clicks on Save and send shopping cart and filled all fields.
 # Save and send the All fields.
 # Enter the customer information.(Firstname,lastname,Zip Code,Place Street).
 # Click on search.

Actual: We are getting Error message on DOB field.

Expected: Customer should be search without DOB Even we enter City, ZIP code.

Please find below screenshot.

Kshitij Kumar Srivastava  added a comment - 
 
this looks like to me a design gap.

i guess when SOHO business customer type was introduce this was missed to make DOB to option over search page.

column968:
16/May/23 6:21 PM;vandana.rajanna@vodafone.com;Outcome from the meeting on 5/16/23- 
 # [@Dipali Gakhare, Vodafone (External)|mailto:dipali.gakhare@vodafone.com] reproduced and explained the scenario.
 # As per [@kshitij.srivastava@dynacommerce.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@dynacommerce.com] – This is not a defect but a design gap as DOB field was mandatory when Agent search by customer data and this was missed for SOHO business customer to make DOB as optional in search page. We will have to raise a demand for further analysis.

1. [@Ajay Yashwant Bhavar, Vodafone|mailto:ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com] to send a mail to Andreas keeping [~metin.celik@vodafone.com] in loop explaining the scenario to raise a demand for further analysis.;;;

column967:
12/May/23 2:59 PM;bhavesh.renpara1@vodafone.com;Hi,

Ideally permanent account number only can be reflected in Omnius if OGW sends to us.

*I1010 - UpdateTemporaryCustomerID:​*
# This service pushes permanent customer ID from OGW to OSE.​
# OGW pushes message to amdocs.ogw.customerupdate queue.​
# I1010 service pulls message from this queue and puts in dyna.ose.setstatus queue.​
# status daemon pulls message from dyna.ose.setstatus queue and updates in table “catalog_package”->parent_account_number

So check and share the below logs to check if first OGW has sent permanent account number.
- OIL archive logs for service I1010. For the day when the permanent account number was pushed by OGW. 
- Status daemons logs to check further if received account number was  update.

[~bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com] As far as i know process(mentioned above) for updating permanent account number at our end should same for Unity media as well. But you can double check with our BA.

Regards,
Bhavesh Renpara;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | CR-525 | Ticket status is not getting updated in Cassandra DB service table.
column42:
We are currently conducting CR-525 testing. During the downtime testing phase, we have noticed that if a user attempts specific services multiple times, they will be locked (expected result) and the ticket status will marked as open in the Cassandra DB. However, we are encountering an issue in closing the ticket. We are unable to close the ticket and until the ticket is closed, we are unable to perform CR-525 testing on that user.

 

*Steps to reproduce:* 
 # Login to Telesales/Retail channel as per requirement
 # Perform any services mentioned in table.
 # perform it more than transaction mentioned in table.
 # user should get locked.

 

*Expected result:* Ticket status should be closed in Cassandra DB.

*Actual Result:* Ticket status Remains open in Cassandra DB.
column413:
Ticket which is created because user is locked is not getting closed automatically (technical ticket)

Unable to complete testing for CR-525

Services table is not supposed to be updated (its a reference table) and the status should be updated in fraud_state table 

Please share o2awf log from relevant date and logs from ticket stream in sky smart. 

Please also share result of below queries:

sky cassandra DB:

select * from jesi_sst.fraud_state where "AgentId"='<agent used for testing>';

 

o2a oracle DB:

SELECT jesi_wf_task_trc.task_id, 
jesi_wf_task_trc.PROCESS_ID,
jesi_wf_task_trc.TASK_STATUS,
jesi_wf_task_trc.COMPLETION_DATE,
sky_pub_tktdtl.TKTNUM,
sky_pub_tktdtl.RCVDTM,
sky_pub_tktdtl.COMIND,
sky_pub_tktdtl.COMDTM,
sky_pub_tktdtl.STTCOD,
sky_pub_tktdtl.estx38 agentid,

sky_pub_tktdtl.estx41 LockServiceName
FROM sky_pub_tktdtl, 
jesi_wf_task_trc,
JESI_WF_PROCESS_PARAM_TRC,
JESI_WF_PROCESS_TRC 
WHERE sky_pub_tktdtl.estx41='<service name used for testing>'
AND sky_pub_tktdtl.estx38='<agent id used for testing>'
AND JESI_WF_PROCESS_PARAM_TRC.ENVCOD = 'OGW'
AND JESI_WF_PROCESS_PARAM_TRC.LEVCOD = 'L2'
AND JESI_WF_PROCESS_PARAM_TRC.PROCESS_ID = jesi_wf_task_trc.PROCESS_ID
AND JESI_WF_PROCESS_TRC.PROCESS_ID = jesi_wf_task_trc.PROCESS_ID
AND JESI_WF_PROCESS_PARAM_TRC.LEVCOD = sky_pub_tktdtl.LEVCOD
AND JESI_WF_PROCESS_PARAM_TRC.ENVCOD = sky_pub_tktdtl.ENVCOD
AND JESI_WF_PROCESS_PARAM_TRC.TKTNUM = sky_pub_tktdtl.TKTNUM;

Hello! This is our input requested from the last call :
For the submit order flow, we have the following three services: submit order, send document and support order .

column978:
12/May/23 1:05 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Divya Kumbla added a comment -
 
 
Hello [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com]  , just checked the issue

As per the multimapper defined if we have C_basic in the cart along with other tariff ,the tivano option addon 's gets added based on the service expression

If cart has C_basic ,TivanoOptionSku is included in SystemAdditionalData only if the service expression satisfies to true

so if the service expression below is satisfied

order.containsProductInCategoryId('FN78') == true and (order.containsProductInCategoryId('FN142') == true or order.containsProductInCategoryId('FN220') == true)

then below is sent in submit order request

<SystemAdditionalData>
<SystemName>FN</SystemName>
<AttributeCode>TivanoOptionSku</AttributeCode>
<AttributeValue>VI002</AttributeValue>
<AttributeAdditionalValue>Tivano/product/option</AttributeAdditionalValue>

</SystemAdditionalData>

!image-2023-05-12-13-04-04-968.png!

Here you see the value going for GPON because, FTTH-GPON belongs to ('FN220') category !image-2023-05-12-13-04-31-124.png!

(C_basic mapped to FN78 category and FTTH-GPON is mapped to FN220 category)

but FTTH-Telekom belongs to FN0454 and there is no service expression defined with this category for C_basic;;;

11/May/23 5:44 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Divya Kumbla added a comment -
 
[~amruta.chougule@vodafone.com]  The existing logic is the access provider having the highest bandwidth will be considered to display relevant details in information tab and if 2 access provider has same higher bandwidth then it check priority.

Scenario 1:To get DTAG details in i information tab DTAG should provide highest bandwidth

eg: DTAG 1000 Mbits/s,GPON 500Mbits/s then DTAG will be shown

Scenario 2:

if DTAG and GPON has same bandwidth ,then priority will be checked

eg DTAG 1000 Mbits/s with priority 1 ,GPON Mbits/s with priority 2 then DTAG will be shown

DTAG 1000 Mbits/s with priority 2 ,GPON Mbits/s with priority 1 then GPON will be shown;;;

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.0 | Dealer code is missing in submit order request for Retail FI agent.
column42:
This issue is happening for almost all FI agents when agent submit order first time for contract generation, Contract summary and document is getting generated successfully.
But when agent is creating second order and trying to submit for contract generation error is coming in submit order request.

Error Message:
<ErrorCode>OGWERR-3000</ErrorCode>
<ErrorDescription>An error was encountered while invoking KIAS AllocateBanAndCtnRequest WS.Details [Error_Code: EAI000132 , Error_Message: DealerCode not provided. , Error_Type: Validation , Error_Severity: E , Error_Information: dealer not provided,Backend Error Code: 443]</ErrorDescription>

Note: This issue is happening only when agent is trying to submit second order with Mobile product.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as FI Agent.
2. Create Mobile Postpaid package.
3. Proceed to checkout and submit order for contract generation.
4. CS and CD retrieved and submit order.

Few technical conclusions from the meeting for DXL API.
 * Now this issue is not there, maybe there was temporary cable backend issue. So, ticket can be closed.
 * Omnius API will continue to send 500 http status code to client(DXL at this moment) in case of any such {*}exception at backend (OGW or next system){*}. Error message would be the once, received from BE.
 * Omnius API will continue to send 500 http status code to client(DXL at this moment) in case of any Omnius internal exception. è This point was not discussed in call, but this is the current behavior for 5XX errors by Omnius API servers to client.
 * Current Omnius behavior is as per the expectation by client, so will not do any further SW changes in Omnius API/OSE SW for error code handling.

*Error Message in I07 logs:* 

<cbc:StatusReasonCode>OIL-TIMEOUT</cbc:StatusReasonCode>
<cbc:StatusReason>A timeout has occurred calling a backend service (OGW). Please contact support if the error persists.</cbc:StatusReason>
</cac:Status>
<lean:Success>false</lean:Success>
</ns0:RetrieveCustomerInfoResponse>

 

*Test Data:*

Cable: 932872380, 906153936, 934709225

Mobile: KS_117235531

DSL: FN_001952884313, FN_001948845091, FN_001927562620, FN_001920757375

 # Login to Telesales/Retail Agent.
 # Search any mobile/cable/dsl customer.
 # After customer if found, click on that customer.
 # While retrieving the customer, we are getting above error in I07 logs.

 

 

*Expected result:*  **  There should be no error visible during customer retrieval and agent                                    should be able to perform ILS on that customer.

 I tried to replicate the error scenario on my local as well as ST environment but enable to get such error.
I can notice, the given agent’s wrong login attempt is more then configured Wrong Password Attempts but still the agent is not locked.

!9d2b67a2-9a75-4182-878c-76051e411c2d.png!

Current Scenario (Happy scenario) : If agent try to login with wrong password till configured Wrong Password Attempts then login attempt increase and agent will locked.

If we unlock the agent then the login attempt reset to Zero.

So now on ACC, Login attempt is more than configured Wrong Password Attempts and agent is unlocked, ideally this not suppose to be happen.

The point is are we using some default database (seed) in which this wrong data is present.

And I believe there is User Management script which correcting/adjusting data, So are we using that on ACC env.

column413: Cable E2E orders are not possible .
column658:
Problem occurs because 'EMTAKOAX' has been added as Accessory to the material table.
The device size of an accessory is "NOT_RELEVANT".

ParcelSizeDeterminator.findSmallestFittingParcelDescription fails because BusinessConfig table TBL_PARCEL_UPPER_BOUNDARY does not include values for "NOT_RELEVANT" devices.

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.0 | Orders are stuck in Initial state (IN THE FIRST QUEUE).
column42:
All our Telesales and Retail new activation and ILS orders are stuck in Initial queue, due to this issue Order processing cannot be completed end to end as OGW is not triggering order flow after submit order request.

Please find below screenshots from Order Manager:

 !image-2023-04-13-12-25-01-359.png|thumbnail! 

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as Telesales/Retail channel.
2. Create Mobile/DSL/Kable order.
3. Proceed to checkout and clicks on generate contract summary button.
4. Contract summary generated, submit order.
5. Verify order logs in OGW.

Actual:  Orders are stuck in Initial state (IN THE FIRST QUEUE).

Expected: Orders should not stuck in Initial state (IN THE FIRST QUEUE) and OGW should trigger order flow further to backend.

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.0 | Retail order failing in SendDocumentRequest with exception.
column42:
Our Retail orders are failing in send document request with below error, Due to this issue, order submission is not possible as it’s blocking on create contract summary page.
Please find attached senddocument request and submit order request logs.

Error Message:
  <env:Text xml:lang="en">org.springframework.oxm.UnmarshallingFailureException: JAXB unmarshalling exception; nested exception is javax.xml.bind.UnmarshalException
- with linked exception:
[org.xml.sax.SAXParseException; cvc-complex-type.2.4.a: Invalid content was found starting with element '{http://www.arcor.net/outputmgmt/EPSM-OutputMgmt-002:externeId}'. One of '{http://www.arcor.net/outputmgmt/EPSM-OutputMgmt-002:auftraggeber}' is expected.]</env:Text>
      </env:Reason>

Order ID: 689869

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
2. Create Mobile/DSL/Kable order.
3. Proceed to checkout and clicks on generate contract button.
4. Getting error in GenerateContract Mode submit order response.

Actual: Retail order failing in SendDocumentRequest with exception.

Expected: SendDocumentRequest should not fail and agent should be able to submit order.
column413: Agent cannot submit order as Contract summary creation is failing in send document request with exception.

column1: OSF | ACC2 | Unitymedia - For  migration with more than 3 numbers the one time fee is missing in the summary
column42:
For unity DSL migration Porting with more than 3 number, wrong pricing is shown in Summary

 
 # Porting of 4 numbers has a onetime charge of 9.99
 # Porting of 5 numbers has a onetime charge of 18.98
 # Porting of 6 numbers has a onetime charge of 29,97

 

!image-2023-03-06-19-49-58-214.png!

 

In the checkout in the order overview before creation of contract summary the one time charge section is missing. 
4Rufnummern is only shown with 0 Euro which is correct for MONTHLY charge – but there is no one time charge section.

!image-2023-03-06-19-52-01-988.png!

Therefore it is also missing on the contract summary

!image-2023-03-06-19-53-59-359.png!

 

There is a very old defect where this fee was missing on the contract summary only, but part of the order overview. There you can see it was working in the past.

column1: OSF-API - Search customer with German character (umlauts) is not possible
column42:
On search customer with german characters (äöü) the search customer return 400.

Example from *ACC2*

1. German Charcater in firstName

*Get Request*

[https://osf-telesales-int-acc2.vodafone.de:8443/api/customer/v3/search?originator=qaosfapi&correlationId=4f13018a-956e-4392-9adf-aba08f6f038c&givenName=J]ürgenr&familyName=Gabler&birthDate=1957-03-11&postalCode=93343

 

*Response*

{     "code": "400",     "reason": "Bad request.",     "message": "givenName field(s) are mandatory or format is not correct or value is not in allowed list." }

 

2. German character in familyName

*Get Request*

[https://osf-telesales-int-acc2.vodafone.de:8443/api/customer/v3/search?originator=qaosfapi&correlationId=4f13018a-956e-4392-9adf-aba08f6f038c&givenName=Oliver&familyName=Pr]{*}ö{*}bstel&birthDate=1969-02-11&postalCode=91325

*Response*

{     "code": "400",     "reason": "Bad request.",     "message": "familyName field(s) are mandatory or format is not correct or value is not in allowed list." }

 

 
On search with Customer Id the response contains the name with german character (in attachment)

column1: OSF | Wave 7.2 | ACC2 | VVL: Future dated discount product getting removed from shopping cart in case of Mobile contract prolongation.
column42:
We are performing Prolongation with New SIM as Physical SIM on existing Mobile customer which is having VFPASS product (Discount) and effective date is future date in Telesales channel.

Here we observed that after performing VVL, VFPASS product (Discount) are getting removed from shopping cart.

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1)Login to Omnius Telesales/retail

2)Search existing customer

3)Retrieve customer data

4)check OIL (I07)logs for AgreementEffectiveDate of the product

5)Perform change tariff and click on weiter

6)Observe products in extended shopping cart

 

*Actual Result:* Future dated product(discount) are getting removed from shopping cart in mobile VVL flow

*Expected Result:* Future dated product(discount) should not remove from shopping cart in mobile VVL flow

*Test data:*

Customer id= 106877273

column971:
10/Feb/23 2:19 PM;oliver.lampert1@vodafone.com;With decision on 9th February from Demand Management (Astrid Hilder) and DT3 it is accepted to GoLive with this bug. 

Root Cause for different behaviour of printing customerID on OM side is different handling of customerID dependent on length of customerID.

1) Dummy customer numbers (zeros) with 9 and 12 chars are lead to suppressing of printing. (example above XsellMob on DSL)

2) Dummy customer numbers (zeros) with 10,11, 13 chars are not covered and lead to printing. (example XsellCable on DSL)

For second case CU for change on OM side is needed.

Expectation: In case of xSell customerNumber should not appear on introduction letter because of new contract.

Magnus takes care.

Defect will stay open until CU is ready and RFA declared. Retest necessary.;;;

column980:
09/Feb/23 12:20 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Divya Kumbla added a comment -
 
 
 
[~natasa.dimovic@vodafone.com]  once a we receive CS_aborted from external system(OM or OGW) we update the status of that offer to CS_Aborted ,So offer will have only one status at a time. CS_Superceded will be overridden by CS_aborted as the latest status send by external system is CS_aborted

there is no question of deciding which status to show, whatever status is available in DB we show the same. Offer holds only one status at a time.

column983:
09/Feb/23 3:45 PM;natasa.dimovic@vodafone.com;We retested again and here a short summary:

*1st issue:* 

When changing/ replacing an offer:
 # Change/ Replace offer in *360 view* with „{*}Bearbeiten{*}” – > 1st CS ID has the Omnius status "{color:#00875a}*CS_Superseded*{color}" - > *OK* (see new updated Word document)
 # Change/ Replace offer with click on „{*}Konfiguration{*}” (go back) – > 1st CS ID has the Omnius status "{color:#00875a}*CS_Superseded*{color}" - > *OK* (see new updated Word document)
 # Change/ Replace with click on „{*}Zurück zum Checkout{*}” – > 1st CS ID has the Omnius status "{color:#de350b}*CS_Aborted*{color}" – > *NOT OK* (see bug description)

Why the behavior is different fo the 3rd case?

*2nd issue:*

From our understanding the Omnius status "CS_Aborted" was implemented with EECC that the customer should have the possibility to reject the Contract Summary via E-Mail. But this was never used, its just implemented and 'dead code'! The customer can only accept the Contract Summary OR the Contract Summary will get the status "CS_Timeout" after some time (depending on the configuration) if the Contract Summary was not accepted.

If this is the case, then the Omnius status CS_Aborted should never be shown. ;;;

column968:
31/Jan/23 4:17 PM;sunil.kumar3@vodafone.com;
Bas Smeets added comment as-


The problem is with options prices that are calculated using mixmatch the maf price goes to zero, so there is no maf price on the item.

In current code we are sending all these options which go to 0 maf as OTC price. This is the same for production code on release/9.14.7

The logic  for options is followed that if no prices are applied and also no discounts are applied(mixmatch is not discount) then we will check if the product is visible (any visibility) then we will send OTC, in case not visible or value “not shown” we will send the REC price.

Im not sure if the expectation is valid here since we are sending OTC also in prod code, this was never a concern.

Since both prices are 0 (maf and price) based on what should the maf even be send? Should it be based on the original product price? This would be a new logic.


;;;
column970:
31/Jan/23 9:54 PM;astrid.hilder@vodafone.com;Hi all, 

Lukas asked me if I can check above mentioned comment as well. From my point of view the misunderstanding lies in current behavior for option prices that a 0 Euro maf is interpreted as "no maf price" and therefore is sending as 0 Euro OTC. 

As above mentioned: "The problem is with options prices that are calculated using mixmatch the maf price goes to zero, so there is no maf price on the item. In current code we are sending all these options which go to 0 maf as OTC price."

But from my point of view this behavior is not correct because the monthly price for a monthly charged option can also be zero. It is definately wrong to show an option with monthly service and monthly price as "one time charge" on contract summary because such an option will be shown every month on the customer bill (with 0 Euro monthly price).

Maybe the mixmatch rules need to be changed... ?

Best regards, Astrid (sorry);;;
column971:
01/Feb/23 9:26 PM;sunil.kumar3@vodafone.com;[~amruta.chougule@vodafone.com]

Timo Hurai 

From my point of view, this is a reject. 

The reasons for this are:

 The logic to sent OTC in case the ‘price’ and ‘maf’ is 0, is already in code for 1,5 years. 

The logic that is 1,5 year in code was never a problem 

There was never a requirement to for example look if there was a ‘price’ or ‘maf’ set for a product before applying the Mixmatch. 

We are 1 day before code freeze so adopting the code now last minute is risky and might impact other scenario’s.

If this needs to be improved, then we could either log an internal improvement or address this to VF and wait for the requirement. ;;;

Well this is not a defect and must be rejected. The current behaviour of banner is working as per US definition.

In my opinion we need an improvement to this banner notification in generic manner.

column973:
18/Jan/23 8:21 PM;sukhdev.singh@vodafone.com;Hi [~arian.ghallaj@vodafone.com] ,

 

Please see the mail response from YairAharon on the same:

"Just to make the example of CUSTOMERID to be clear. Let’s use the following UM (test) data: legacy Customer-ID as 109235205 from the NRW region.

Based on the mapping defined in the confluence page, the CUSTOMERID is formatted as CUMST.UMREGION (region decode: 1= NRW ; 2= HSN ; 3= KBW) + CUMST.CUCNO (legacy Customer-ID).

So the CUSTOMERID identifier in MRT will have the value: {*}{color:#FF0000}1{color}{*}109235205 ."

[^FW_ MRT- UM identifiers.msg]

You need to add region code before the UM Customer Id.

[https://apigee-xtest03.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de/masterRoutingTable/v1/routing//{*}{color:#FF0000}1{color}{*}1003458101?id_type=CUSTOMERID|https://apigee-xtest03.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de/masterRoutingTable/v1/routing//1003458101?id_type=CUSTOMERID&market=NRW]

market is optional parameter.;;;
column974: 18/Jan/23 8:26 PM;shival.gupta1@vodafone.com;[~arian.ghallaj@vodafone.com] Only for UM customers. Omnius retrieves Region->Market value from ValidateAddress response and uses the same while calling MRT.;;;

Id and Id_Type are required parameters.

column1: OSF | ACC2 | wave 7.2 | CR632 | Flexible authentication is failing while performing customer search without Dialer using flexible authentication + MTAN authentication in Retail channel
column42:

Steps to reproduce:

 # Go to 360 view -> data is still masked and button ‘Kunden Authentifizieren’ is shown

the MTAN authentication window is shown at the beginning, and not in the 360 view as expected, this is NOT correct.

column967:
11/Jan/23 6:29 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Regarding Anja Durben it must work like described in the Story OAF-445:

 

Here is the answer from Anja:

 

This is definitely a bug.

VF understanding is: We must have 2 Layers / 2 Steps of Authentication:

 

*Step 1 - First Layer* : *at which time in flow authentication is triggered*

Soft Authentication, Hardauthentication, Flex Authentication

 

Hardauthentication – Authentication directly after the customer search (default)

Soft Authentication – no Authentication at all

Flex Authentication – In 360 view

 

*Step 2- Second Layer:* *which method of authentication must be used*

1) Customer keyword or alternative data (default)

2) 2of X

3) MTAN

4) Service Pin

 

It makes only sence to make a *prioritisation within* the 2 layers.

But not, to prioritise methode (Layer2) over at which time in the flow (Layer1) .

At which time (Layer1) has always higher priority than the methode (Layer2).

 

In the second layer, there can be a priorisation of which methode will be first, second, third if there are more options.

 

*See requirement for MTAN*

[OS-12205 [BUSINESS] As an agent, I want MTAN to replace the existing authentication method for dedicated scenarios, so that VF complies with legal requirements. - Vodafone Global Jira
 # *If* the agent is forced to authenticate the customer at all and if so, *at which point* in the sales flow this should happen is determined by already existing permissions and functionalities outside this epic (such as: hard authentication, soft authentication, no authentication, in future: flex authentication). The new permission for *MTAN Authentication should not change that but only determine how authentication is executed when it is required.* If the MTAN permission is assigned, it is supposed to be the default method. If it is not assigned, the fallback authentication (2 out of 6) should apply.

*See requirement for Flex Authentication:*

[[OAF-445] OMNIUS : UM As a system, create new permission (FLEXIBLE_AUTHENTICATION), So that Agent flexible to authenticate customer in sales process. - Vodafone Global Jira|https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fjira.sp.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOAF-445&data=05%7C01%7CNina.Pickl%40vodafone.com%7C86eb42a760a1405fd88a08daf3cf8be9%7C68283f3b84874c86adb3a5228f18b893%7C0%7C0%7C638090369998688654%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=aKcmV8dOUCaJQOTCMrkXG6RDVTghYlXNk2qoRq68ax8%3D&reserved=0]

 

Future topic wave7.1
FLEXIBLE_AUTHENTICATION + MTAN_AUTHENTICATION
Agent see the Kunden authentication button in 360
system consider MTAN_AUTHENTICATION

 

Please contact Anja , if you need further support.

 ;;;
column968:
12/Jan/23 3:12 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;[~nina.pickl@vodafone.com] [~alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com] 
 
Kshitij Kumar Srivastava added a comment -
I also agree while implemention of CR632 {{MTAN_AUTHENTICATION}} was not in picture. so far it was never tested in CR632

also +Additional note+ in US OAF-445 was wrong for usecase MTAN + FLEX.

So according to authenticaton priority ruling
If Agent logged in Reatil and has both permission MTAN + FLEX then system first attempt MTAN authentication. 
In case MTAn fails system follow the fallback mean system will considder FLEX.

Note: with FLEX_AUTHENTICATION permisson if Agent lands to customer search page, then he can simply skip authentication on search page and continue in sales flow, when he lands to Customer 360 view page Agent must autheticate customer (mean ‘Kunden authentifizieren’ should appears over 360 page) 
And sytem should force Agent to autheticate customer before continue the sales flow.

So conclusion here 
This defect must be rejected. the expectation is incorrect.;;;

The response time from some requests is more than 20s and some time more than 30s. It is possible to determin in which point of the flow the delay is present?

03/Aug/23 4:24 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~dipali.gakhare@vodafone.com] [~nicusor.vintan@vodafone.com] 
Bas Smeets added a comment -
 
 
A bit of background on this ticket.
 # This defect was raised to indicate the API performance has gone bad

 # It was established that the API test results heavily rely on the services response times, therefore the correlationId from the test has to be present in the serviceCallStatistics.log, we can then see the time it takes for the service to respond and correlate that with the test.

 # It was told by VF that the correlationId are not getting logged correctly. (current problem)

 

Next: I checked the fact that the correlationId is not being logged correctly when passing this in the request through jmeter. I am able to see exactly the correlationId’s that i am sending in the jmeter requests. I did the tests for search and 2 installedbase gigacombi requests. All are showing the corerlationId as being send in the request.

See screenshots and see adjusted for local jmeter script below.

Are we sure the correct logs are being retrieved? Since we are triggering this towards the DXL api server there it will connect to a ose instance (configured in .env field OSE_BOOTSTRAP) on the same machine.

 

Suggestion:

Setup a call to perform the test and retrieve the logs from DXL api server.

!ea7bb05e-80d8-45ce-b16b-cc50f227005d.png!

!3fd1f7d8-7011-4c46-8637-69338f40d203.png!

column986:
04/Sep/23 5:26 PM;joachim.heiber@vodafone.com;Meetings with TechM and Production and Performance team happened.
Conclusion: 
 - API Team will concentrate on functional API tests
 - Performance Teams (VF, TechM, amdocs) are responsible and are verifying the performance related behaviour of OSF
 - If there is a request for single measurements of single requests, then LNP environment should be used. Response times on ACC environments are related to too many components like backend systems and other non OSF systems.

Therefore we decide to close this ticket and to not continue the investigation which is going around since december 2022. Performance tests and their investigations will be handled by performance team.;;;

The problem is that the wrong value is set in case of multistack orders. 

These are the values for *KundennummerArt* we need to set for the cable part towards OM in case it is unity.

UnityNW
UnityHE
UnityBW

 
||Region||OGW global_ID prefix // TargetSystem||OGW service address region||OM KundennummerArt||
|*Nordrhein-Westfalen*|*UN*|*UME-NRW*|*UnityNW*|
|Hessen|UH|UME-HSN|UnityHE|
|Baden-Württemberg|UB|UME-KBW|UnityBW|
|Vodafone Kabel Deutschland|KD|UNKNOWN, R01, R02, ... ,R09|VKD|

So if this is a bundle order with Cable and Mobile, currently it is set to VKD althought it is in unitymedia region. 
Maybe you can reproduce on your environment by creating a multistack order and check the logs 

I placed a new order with mobile and cable - Omnius order ID *917483*

column1: OSF | ACC2 |Telesales (IPCC & Avaya) | setPermissions call is still on standby although SetOrderStatus and UM customer number are reflected in OGW
column42:
setPermissions call is still on standby although SetOrderStatus and UM customer number are reflected in OGW, 

 

System CRM value is correctly populated for the this order.

 

Anaylsis:

IPCC will sent an upper Case TransactionID to OMNIUS that will then call OGW service setPermission with an upper case transaction id in UniqueTransactionID.

Internally IPCC saves the transaction id lower case. This will lead to a lower case Transaction ID in the call to OGW service ArchiveFiles.

 

Functionality in OGW:
 # If ArchiveFiles service call comes first and SetPermission call comes later. In this case it will work fine as ogw has updated sql query in upper case.
 # If Set permission call comes first and ArchiveFiles call come later. In this case SetPermission flow will wait forever because transaction ids are not in same case.

 

FIX:

IPCC will always sent a lower case transaction_id with fix IPCCWDE-346.

Delivery to IPCC Test atarting 17.04.2023 will be available together with OSF Wave 8.0. 

 

OGW fix for SQl is now superfluous:

column971:
09/Nov/22 2:15 PM;singireddy.reddy@vodafone.com;In case the Customer also belongs to Unity Media i.e TargetSystem has value UN/UH/UB then flow is extended by below triggers.
 * Check in *VOICE_FILES_TO_PROCESS* table is there is an existence of MetadataFile and VoiceFile for the input UniqueTransactionID.
 ** If there is a FileName present then OGW will do as follows:
 *** Call CreateOptStatement service of Anypoint
 **** Input to Anypoint: *optStatementContent*
 **** Output from Anypoint: *CreateOptStatementResponse*
 *** Call CreateVoice Serice of Anypoint
 **** Input to Anypoint: *OptFileName*
 **** Output from Anypoint: *na*
 ** If FileName is not found then OGW is waiting for message *ARCHIVE_VOICE_FILE* from the ArchiveFile API which is triggered by the calling System with the uniqueTransactionID.
 *** After receiving File Name then OGW will do as follows:
 **** Call CreateOptStatement service of Anypoint
 ***** Input to Anypoint: *optStatementContent*
 ***** Output from Anypoint: *CreateOptStatementResponse*
 **** Call CreateVoice Serice of Anypoint
 ***** Input to Anypoint: *OptFileName*
 ***** Output from Anypoint: *na*;;;
