column1: OSF | Wave7.1 | ACC1&ACC2 | Telesales | Unitymedia orders with manual approval do not reach status completed
column42:
In case unitymedia order is not approved automatically in RNS, we are missing the order status and customer number in OSF.

Steps:
 * start order for unitymedia in Telesales (e.g. with KIP)
 * Submit order and check weborder ID in IAV
 * Identify reference ID is created in unity backend but order is not approved automatically
 * Approve order with the given reference ID in unitymedia backend (No new order is created! Weborder ID is set as external reference)
 * Check status / customer number in VKD and OGW -> information for customer ID is missing and status is not completed

Expected:

Also for manual approved orders the status is set to completed and customer ID is transferred via VKD to OSF

07/Dec/23 1:51 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Updates:

 

OGW needs the customer number in case Unity Manual Approval Orders in Telesales and Retails, which should be provided from VKD to OGW within the existing FulfillmentStarted Request.

 

The customer number is atm provided only for Auto Approval Orders, but missing for Manual Approval orders, therefore the document cannot be archived and the OGW processing remain in status pending (the VKD status is SUCCESS but the orders don't get Sucecss status in OSF Fronend):

An error was encountered while invoking ScanView-SaveDocument WS. Details [Error_Code: HTTPOutbound_0001, Error_Message: Received a fault from processing server for service '/ScanView-001/SaveDocument': An invalid number format or number value was encountered.

Note: Retail Manual Approval Orders don't have this issue because the call to oneDMS/Customernumber is not needed for the E2E flow. They get the Status Success.

 

As the customer number has not been sent for Manual Approval Order until now, a new PST change is required.

I will take the topic with me and check if we can request this change at the PST CAT train, Team Ash(Benjamin Sachse) or Nora.

 

The new requirement should contain following information:
 * no difference between retail and telesales from cable perspective
 * example set status messages received by OSF
 * fulfilment started from manual approval 
 * fulfilment started from automatic approval 


 * explanation on
 * what you clicked to create the manual approval order
 * how to approve the manual approval order

Will update here once it is clear how to process with the new change.;;;

column1: Wave 8.0_ CR needed || OSF | ACC1 & ACC2 | UPC VASSECURE should not be send for unity orders in Retail
column42:
UPC VASSECURE should not be send for Retail,
 because it is linked to a mandatory / non deselectable option 
 in cablemaster. Therefore cablemaster adds this option always again automatically and there are double UPC Codes -> order goes in manual approval
 For CC / Telesales it is preselected but deselectable. Even if it will be deselected in OSF, Cablemaster will add it again as default value and customer will have wrong products in place

 

Steps to recreate : 
 # Open OSF and search and unity address.
 # select any unity product and complete the order.
 # Check in RNS / IAV if the order is Auto approved or manual approved
column413:
Retail order has to be approved manually
Telesales order includes Security package even if removed in OSF
Workaround: we are using channel ID WS for now until new CR is implemented

column966:
26/Oct/22 8:08 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;The functionality is related to the usage of channnel ID RT and CC.

It has to be clarified if we activate the channel ID in Production or if we leave it with WS Websales

*+Option 1:+*

- wir bleiben in Produktion auf channel ID WS

-> es ist zu prüfen ob es Unterschiede im Angebot von Web und Retail/ Telesales gibt (besonders bei Kampagne)
 -> wenn ein UPC für Web optional ist aber für OSF default ist das kein Problem – hauptsache es gibt das Produkt/ die Option für Web
 Risiko: Auf der ACC ist der Wert WS nicht mehr gesetzt, und es bleibt keine Zeit für ein Regressionstesting Neukunden GigaZuhause E2E / allerdings ist das wie gesagt schon seit Februar so

 

*+Option 2:+*

- wir stellen um auf RT/ CC

-> Arbeitsanweisung für Telesales: Das Sicherheitspaket +darf nicht abgewählt werden+ in OSF. Wenn jemand bei WW Line die Option nicht möchte, muss ein anderer Eingangskanal gewählt werden als OSF

-> Retail darf nicht gelauncht werden bevor das Problem mit dem doppelt gebuchten UPC behoben ist 
 Risiko: Wenn das Sicherheitspaket abgewählt wird ist die Contract Summary nicht identisch mit der Auftragsbestätigung

 

Generell brauchen wir eine Lösung für die Thematik und vermutlich dafür noch mal Entwicklung, aber die Entscheidung ist jetzt erstmal auf Basis GigaZuhause zu treffen.;;;

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Telesales | Tariff list is empty for KUD products when tried to place along with KIP product(Reg Error Message) or TV product
column42:
Empty tariff list  was shown while placing a KUD product along with KIP product on unitymedia region adress

and also same issue when placing KUD Product with TV Product as well

Expected : Tariff list should not be empty. KUD product should be selectable but then error message should be displayed as it is not allowed to book KIP and KUD on unitymedia adress in same order

 

Steps to recreate :
 # Take an unitymedia address in Telesales 
 # Search the address.
 # Move to package configurator and select any KIP product.
 # Move to package configurator and check for the KUD products.

 

!image-2022-10-13-15-44-12-723.png|width=2064,height=647!

 

So with this defect the expected result should be 

1) KUD products should be listed after we have selected KIP Unitymedia 

2) After selection KUD product error message should be shown because it is not allowed to mix KIP Unity and KUD products in one order

3) Error message should state clearly why it is not possible to mix the products in one order (improvement, taken from discussion of OS-22095)
column413:
Agent might be confused because its not clear why no tarifs are displayed.

No wrong booking can happen, but normally agent expects the tarifs to be visible and when selecting a tarif, error should be displayed to explain why products cannot be booked together.
column658: Availability of corresponding products adapted and new pop-up messages created
column965:
20/Dec/22 4:17 PM;moritz.laudahn@vodafone.com;Hi [~singireddy.reddy@vodafone.com],
this is works as designed. At a Unitymedia address you currently cannot book KIP/TV in combination with KUD.

Cable and Unitymedia still have separated backends.
 * You need a Unitymedia customer for booking KIP/TV at an Unitymedia address.
 * You need a Cable customer for booking KUD (no matter the address).

Both cannot be handled together as part of the same order.;;;

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
2. Create Mobile order with Multi-packages.
3. Submit order.
4. Verify all packages failed in KIAS.
5. Verify Completed-Failed Response received in OGW.

Actual: Partial Completed (Zum Teil erfolgreich) status is being sent on order level even if all packages failed with Completed-Failed status reason.

Expected: Completed-Failed status should be sent on order level if all packages failed with Completed-Failed status reason.

column1: CR: FAST-720 CR675 - Retail - Wrong data in SEPA mandate at an order with different Account owner
column42:
Browser: Chrome
 Environment: ACC1 (test1b)
 Test address: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München

 

+Actual result+: Wrong data in SEPA mandate at an order with different Account owner. The customer is displayed as the account owner (Name des Zahlenden)

 

+Expected result+: The account owner should be displayed as the account owner (Name des Zahlenden)

   

 +Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to ACC1 - Retail
 * enter any address for creating a new Fixnet or Cable customer, e. g.: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Angebote mit Vertrag"
 * select any MOB hardware
 * select any MOB tariff
 * continue with the order until the Payment Details
 * enter any NEW IBAN
 * select "Abweichender Kontoinhaben and enter the data of a different account owner

!image-2022-07-05-15-11-13-042.png!

 

 
 * open the contract document

    -> in the SEPA mandate the wrong person is shown as the account owner --> *NOK*

 

!image-2022-07-05-15-12-20-170.png!
column413: The name of the Different Account Holder is not printed in the SEPA Mandat document in Retail. Its only for the different account holder scenario, who has to sign then the document.

column1: Category Import: Broken bundles after partial stack import
column42:
*Status*
 * Import of a category will erase/replace all IDs (example: Mobile or Fixed Net/DSL or Cable)
 * Those old IDs are still being used by other categories, also new tariffs have no counterpart in for exmple: bundles  
 * Old IDs are still being referenced in dependent categories (example: Bundles broken because of old IDs after Mobile only partial import)

*Goal*
 * Please resolve the "missing ID"  issue with least impact to import duration.

*Some options/Ideas*
 * *Synchronization of IDs:* The number of categories being imported stay the same but their IDs are being updated and syncronized with all interdependant categories.
 * *Synchronization of Import:* If absolutely necessary import of categories due to hash change might need to trigger import of other categories, too (_Example:_ Mobile category import triggers Bundle category import). This is the worst solution, as it impacts runtime.
 * *Keep old IDs:* Only provide new SKUs with new IDs. Keep the IDs of existing SKUs.
 * *Alternative:* PLease feel free to design your own solution to this

Please keep me posted about the path of resolvement and communicate about resolvement path.
